      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The Supreme Court's interpretation of the 2nd Amendment has been a conservative stronghold, but it's a misinterpretation of the founders' intent. The Founding Fathers were heavily influenced by the British Bill of Rights, which protected gun rights, but they didn't explicitly state that the right to bear arms was absolute. In fact, the 2nd Amendment's text is often seen as a compromise between those who wanted a militia-based army and those who wanted individual rights. The Court's current interpretation, which has been shaped by conservative justices, is more of a modern-day political agenda to expand gun rights and limit government control, rather than a faithful adherence to the founders' original intent.",
